  "texts": [
    "This choice was motivated by the library's robustness, ease of use, and the active support community, making it a well-suited tool for conducting RL experiments.The StableBaselines3 framework provides RL algorithms with a suite of action spaces.",
    "Through the OpenAI gym [120] library for Python, this framework includes several types of spaces for both actions and observations:‚ÄĘ Dictionary Spaces: A compilation of various spaces organized as a dictionary.‚ÄĘ Discrete Spaces: A set comprising a finite number of integers.‚ÄĘ Box Spaces: Spaces that are continuous in nature.‚ÄĘ MultiDiscrete Spaces: Formed by the cartesian product of several discrete spaces.‚ÄĘ MultiBinary Spaces: Spaces characterized by a binary format, with dimensions specified by an n-dimensional shape.The goal of the RL agent is to navigate a dynamic environment while avoiding collisions, a critical component for the safety of robots in our case.",
    "We explore Name Box Discrete Multidiscrete Multibinary MultiProcessingARS 1 ‚úď ‚úď ‚úď A2C ‚úď ‚úď ‚úď ‚úď ‚úď DDPG ‚úď ‚úď DQN ‚úď ‚úď HER ‚úď ‚úď ‚úď PPO ‚úď ‚úď ‚úď ‚úď QR-DQN 1 ‚úď ‚úď ‚úď RecurrentPPO 1 ‚úď ‚úď ‚úď ‚úď SAC ‚úď ‚úď TD3 ‚úď ‚úď TQC 1 ‚úď ‚úď TRPO 1 ‚úď ‚úď ‚úď ‚úď ‚úď Maskable PPO 1 ‚úď ‚úď ‚úď ‚úďTable 5.3: RL Algorithms and Their Compatible Action Spaces in StableBase-lines3 the efficacy of different RL algorithms in learning policies that can safely and efficiently guide an agent through a series of movements while minimizing the risk of collisions.The RL agent operates within a custom gym environment designed to simulate collision avoidance scenarios.",
    "The environment, implemented in the Colli-sionAvoidanceEnv class for the CD case study and CollisionAvoidanceEnv 6DOF for a six-Degrees Of Freedom scenario, features high-dimensional continuous state spaces representing the positions of objects, and discrete action spaces encoding potential movements.",
    "The objective of the agent is to select actions that alter the objects' positions to avoid collisions."
